claim.claim-text:
A process comprising:
a) providing a biomass and a hyperthermophilic microorganism;
b) degrading said biomass in the presence of a cell density of said microorganism of greater than 109 cell/ml under conditions such that degradation products are produced.

A process comprising:
a) providing a biomass that contains a pathogen and a population of at least one genus of a hyperthermophilic organism;
b) culturing said population of at least one genus of a hyperthermophilic organism under anaerobic conditions on said biomass at a temperature of 80°C or higher;
c) maintaining said culture at temperature of 80°C or higher so that said pathogens are destroyed to provide a decontaminated biomass residue; and
d) processing said decontaminated biomass residue.
